mspace><mml:msub><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">O</mml:mi><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:msub></mml:mrow><mml:mo>&hellip;</mml:mo><mml:msub><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">O</mml:mi><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">L</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">&theta;</mml:mi><mml:mspace width="0.25em"></mml:mspace></mml:mrow></mml:mfenced></mml:math><span class="equ">E37</span></div><p id="p60">Given <span class="inline-formula"><mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" id="m266"><mml:msub><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">&gamma;</mml:mi><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">t</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mfenced open="(" close=")"><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">i</mml:mi></mml:mfenced></mml:math></span> and <span class="inline-formula"><mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" id="m267"><mml:msub><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">&zeta;</mml:mi><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">t</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mfenced open="(" close=")" separators=","><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">i</mml:mi><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">j</mml:mi></mml:mfenced></mml:math></span>, the anticipated number of transitions from state <span class="inline-formula"><mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" id="m268"><mml:msub><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">s</mml:mi><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">i</mml:mi></mml:msub></mml:math></span> during the path is written as</p><div id="df_E38" class="formula panel"><mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" specific-use="web-only" id="m269"><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">E</mml:mi><mml:mfenced open="(" close=")"><mml:mrow><mml:msub><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">&gamma;</mml:mi><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">t</mml:mi></mml:msub><mml:mfenced open="(" close=")"><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">i</mml:mi></mml:mfenced></mml:mrow></mml:mfenced><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:munderover><mml:mo>&sum;</mml:mo><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">t</mml:mi><mml:mo>=</mml:mo><mml:mn>1</mml:mn></mml:mrow><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">L</mml:mi><mml:m